        <updateDate>2021-06-15T14:52:01Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Home Lead Safety Tax Credit Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill allows owners of eligible dwelling units a new tax credit through 2024 for 50% of the lead hazard reduction activity costs for each such unit, up to an aggregate of $4,000 per unit. An <i>eligible dwelling unit</i> is any unit located in the United States that was placed in service before 1978. </p> <p>The bill (1) specifies the types of lead hazard reduction activity costs eligible for the credit, including risk assessment and abatement costs; and (2) limits the amount of the credit in any taxable year to $3,000 for specified abatement measures and $1,000 for interim lead control measures.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
